    <text>
        <body>
            <div>
                <opener><salute>D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Sir</salute></opener>
                <p>Many thanks for y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> late favor &amp;c. I rejoice to
                    hear that y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> copy of <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0009">my voyage</title></bibl> is going at last to <persName ref="pe0246">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Pope</persName> I am in hopes
                    that <persName ref="pe0156">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Low</persName> goes
                    on well &amp; will arrive safe to you with his treasures </p>
                <closer><salute>I am D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Sir <lb/>y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> obed<hi rend="superscript">t</hi> Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi></salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant</persName></signed>
                <dateline>april 4<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> 1775.</dateline></closer>

                <postscript>
                    <p>Is there ever a plan of the <placeName ref="pl0229">Glasgow</placeName>
                        <placeName ref="pl1102">new canal</placeName> that c<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> be inclosed in a Letter.</p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
